                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant, T</hi> 11.) On 21st June I saw the prisoner offering this watch to pawn, at Uxbridge—he said he bought it of two men—I said, "Your woman stole it from a man at Hounslow"—he said, "She was with a man, and she gave me the watch"—he has lived with her three years—he told me if I went I should find her at Harrow—I went there, but they know me, and she was put out the back way.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I want to get rid of that woman—she gave me the watch to pawn—it had no glass or hands.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
